summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance Number 21724, entitled: "An Ordinance providing for the improvement of Lots Three (3), Four (4) and Five (5), all in Block One (1), Cable Line Addition, all in the City of Seattle, by filling the same as a sanitary measure and by fixing and establishing the grades thereof all in accordance with Resolution No. 2152, and 2285 of the City Council of the City of Seattle, and providing for the payment therefor by the mode of "Payment by Bonds," as provided by the laws of the State of Washington and the Charter and Ordinances of the City of Seattle, and declaring an emergency.," approved September 14th, 1909.
